$ apigear prj --help
The prj command allows you to create a new project and manage it.

Usage:
  apigear prj [flags]
  apigear prj [command]

Available Commands:
  create      Create a new document inside current project
  edit        Edit a project in the default editor (vscode)
  import      Import a project from a directory
  info        Show project information
  init        Initialize a new project
  open        Open a project in studio
  pack        Pack a project
  recent      Show recent projects
  share       Share a project

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for prj

Global Flags:
      --config string   config file (default is $HOME/.apigear.yaml)
      --dry-run         dry-run
      --env string      environment (development, production, staging) (default "development")
  -v, --verbose         verbose output

Use "apigear prj [command] --help" for more information about a command.
